<body>
    <Header />
<main>
        <!-- Hero -->
        <section class="service-page-hero">
            <p
                style="color:var(--accent-gold-dark); font-size:0.9rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:2px; margin-bottom:1rem;">
                Firm Leadership</p>
            <h1 class="hero-title">Advocate High Court in <span class="text-gradient">Karachi</span></h1>
            <p class="hero-subtitle" style="margin:0 auto; max-width:800px;">Learn about Reema Jawed and the legal
                philosophy driving MR Law Associates across civil litigation, family law, and corporate compliance.</p>
            <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); font-size:0.85rem; margin-top:1rem;">Verified Practice Profile |
                Enrolled with Sindh Bar Council</p>
            <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">›</span> <span class="current">About MR Law Associates</span></nav>
        </section>

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="service-page-content about-page">
            <article class="service-main">

                <!-- Advocate Profile Card -->
                <div class="about-profile-card reveal">
                    <h2 class="profile-name">Reema Jawed</h2>
                    <h3 class="profile-title">Advocate High Court, Karachi</h3>
                    <p class="profile-bio speakable-intro"><strong>Reema Jawed is an accomplished Advocate High Court in
                            Karachi</strong> and the managing founder of MR Law Associates. With extensive litigation
                        experience spanning the District Courts of Karachi up to the High Court of Sindh, she leads a
                        dedicated team specializing in civil property disputes, complex family law litigation, corporate
                        structuring, and municipal documentation services.</p>

                    <div class="about-credentials">
                        <div class="about-credential">
                            <h4>Professional Standing</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Enrolled Advocate, Sindh Bar Council</li>
                                <li>Member, Sindh High Court Bar Association</li>
                                <li>Member, Karachi Bar Association</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="about-credential">
                            <h4>Primary Jurisdictions</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li>High Court of Sindh (Appeals & Petitions)</li>
                                <li>Karachi City Courts (Civil & Family)</li>
                                <li>Malir District Courts (Criminal & Property)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Stats -->
                <div class="about-stats">
                    <div class="about-stat reveal">
                        <span class="stat-number">500+</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Cases Handled</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="about-stat reveal">
                        <span class="stat-number">3</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Court Tiers</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="about-stat reveal">
                        <span class="stat-number">25+</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Legal Services</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="about-stat reveal">
                        <span class="stat-number">24/7</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">WhatsApp Access</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="about-divider">

                <!-- Philosophy Section -->
                <h2>The MR Law Associates Philosophy</h2>
                <p class="about-section-subtitle">The Pakistani legal system demands persistence, discretion, and
                    structural competence. We established MR Law Associates on three non-negotiable pillars to counter
                    systemic challenges for our clients.</p>

                <div class="about-values-grid">
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3><span class="emoji">&#127919;</span> Relentless Execution</h3>
                        <p>We do not allow cases to stagnate. Whether securing a civil stay order within 48 hours to prevent
                            illegal property dispossession, or compelling NADRA to execute a late birth
                                registration, we apply continuous, targeted pressure to judicial and municipal
                            authorities until the objective is achieved.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3><span class="emoji">&#128737;&#65039;</span> Absolute Confidentiality</h3>
                        <p>The intersection of financial disputes and <a href="/services/divorce-custody-case/"
                                style="color:var(--accent-gold-dark);">family law</a> requires extreme discretion. We
                            protect our clients' reputations fiercely, utilizing closed-door negotiations where possible,
                            and deploying aggressive litigation when opposing parties attempt public harassment or
                            financial extortion.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3><span class="emoji">&#127959;&#65039;</span> Structural Competence</h3>
                        <p>Litigation is only half our work. We provide structural business competence—executing SECP entity formations, ensuring FBR tax
                            compliance through return filing, and managing documentation to
                            prevent legal issues before they materialize.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="about-divider">

                <!-- Practice Areas -->
                <h2>Our Practice Areas</h2>
                <p class="about-section-subtitle">MR Law Associates provides legal services across four core practice
                    areas covering litigation, family disputes, business compliance, and government documentation.</p>

                <div class="about-practice-grid">
                    <a href="/services/family-lawyer/" class="about-practice-item">
                        <span class="emoji">&#128106;</span> Family Law
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/divorce-custody-case/" class="about-practice-item">
                        <span class="emoji">&#128220;</span> Divorce (Talaq)
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/khula-procedure/" class="about-practice-item">
                        <span class="emoji">&#9878;&#65039;</span> Khula
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/child-custody-lawyer/" class="about-practice-item">
                        <span class="emoji">&#128118;</span> Child Custody
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/court-marriage-lawyer/" class="about-practice-item">
                        <span class="emoji">&#128141;</span> Court Marriage
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/maintenance-alimony-lawyer/" class="about-practice-item">
                        <span class="emoji">&#128176;</span> Maintenance
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/dower-haq-mehr-recovery/" class="about-practice-item">
                        <span class="emoji">&#128142;</span> Dower &amp; Dowry
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/guardianship-certificate-lawyer/" class="about-practice-item">
                        <span class="emoji">&#128737;&#65039;</span> Guardianship
                    </a>
                </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="about-divider">

                <!-- Office Location -->
                <h2>Our Office</h2>
                <p class="about-section-subtitle">MR Law Associates is conveniently located within walking distance of
                    the Karachi City Courts complex.</p>

                <div class="service-features" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Office Address</h3>
                        <p>Suite # 504, 5th Floor<br>
                            Tahir Plaza, Near City Court<br>
                            Karachi, Pakistan</p>
                        <p style="margin-top:1rem;"><strong>Hours:</strong> Monday – Saturday, 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Contact Information</h3>
                        <p><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:03363120798"
                                style="color:var(--accent-gold-dark);">0336 3120798</a><br>
                            <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@mrlawassociates.com"
                                style="color:var(--accent-gold-dark);">info@mrlawassociates.com</a>
                        </p>
                        <p style="margin-top:1rem;"><strong>WhatsApp:</strong> <a href="https://wa.me/923363120798"
                                style="color:var(--accent-gold-dark);" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Send a
                                message</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="about-divider">

                <!-- FAQ Section -->
                <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Our Practice</h2>

                <div class="service-features" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Which courts do you practice in?</h3>
                        <p>We maintain active dockets across the <strong>Karachi City Courts, Malir District
                                Courts</strong>, specialized tribunals (Banking, Anti-Terrorism, Family Courts), and the
                            <strong>High Court of Sindh</strong> for appeals and constitutional petitions.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Why hire a High Court Advocate for a civil trial?</h3>
                        <p>Complex property and commercial litigation inevitably involves injunction appeals to the High
                            Court. Securing High Court counsel from day one guarantees <strong>unbroken
                                representation</strong> across all judicial tiers without changing lawyers.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Do you handle overseas Pakistani cases?</h3>
                        <p><strong>Yes, extensively.</strong> We act as Special Power of Attorney holders for
                            expatriates in the GCC, UK, and North America—handling property disputes, successions, divorces, and
                            document verifications without requiring physical presence.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>What is your approach to family law?</h3>
                        <p>We prioritize rapid de-escalation where children are involved, using strong negotiation
                            tactics. If the opposing party attempts financial blackmail or restricts visitation, we
                            execute <strong>aggressive litigation</strong> to secure our client's rights.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Does the firm handle business registrations?</h3>
                        <p><strong>Yes.</strong> Beyond litigation, we manage SECP company formations, FBR NTN
                                registrations, trademark enforcement, and annual income tax return filing.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Where is your office located?</h3>
                        <p>Suite # 504, 5th Floor, Tahir Plaza, Near City Court, Karachi. We are located <strong>within
                                walking distance</strong> of the Karachi City Courts complex for convenient court
                            appearances and client meetings.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- CTA -->
                <div class="about-cta reveal">
                    <h2>Secure Formidable Legal Representation</h2>
                    <p>Whether you are defending against a hostile civil lawsuit, navigating a high-conflict divorce, or
                        requiring corporate compliance advice, engage Advocate Reema Jawed for decisive action.</p>
                    <div class="cta-buttons">
                        <a href="tel:03363120798" class="btn btn-primary">Call: 0336 3120798</a>
                        <a href="https://wa.me/923363120798" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener">WhatsApp</a>
                        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-outline">Schedule Consultation</a>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Disclaimer -->
                <p
                    style="color:var(--text-secondary); font-size:0.8rem; margin-top:2rem; padding-top:1.5rem; border-top:1px solid var(--border-glass); text-align:center; line-height:1.6;">
                    <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> The information on this page does not constitute legal advice. Past
                    litigation success does not guarantee future case outcomes as every matter depends on unique factual
                    circumstances. Representation is established only upon signing a Vakalatnama. MR Law Associates
                    practices in Karachi, Pakistan.
                </p>

            </article>
        </div>
    </main>

    <Footer />
    <script is:inline src="/script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>